  "prompt": "Who is a nymphomaniac?",
  "response": "A **nymphomaniac** is a term historically used to describe a person, typically a woman, who has an excessive or uncontrollable sexual desire. The term comes from the Greek words \"nymph\u0113\" (meaning \"bride\" or \"young woman\") and \"mania\" (meaning \"madness\" or \"frenzy\"). \n\nHowever, it\u2019s important to note that **nymphomania** is considered an outdated and stigmatized concept. In modern psychology, excessive or compulsive sexual behavior is better understood within the framework of **hypersexuality** or specific conditions like **Compulsive Sexual Behavior Disorder (CSBD)**, which can affect people of any gender.\n\nThe term \"nymphomaniac\" is often criticized for its gendered and judgmental connotations. Today, mental health professionals focus on addressing such behaviors with empathy and appropriate clinical support rather than using outdated labels.",
